Lately I've been trying to rid my life of as many physical artifacts as possible. I'm with Merlin Mann on CDs:

Although I'd extend that line of thinking to DVDs as well. The death of physical media has some definite downsides, but after owning certain movies once on VHS, then on DVD, and finally on Blu-Ray, I think I'm now at peace with the idea of not owning any physical media ever again, if
